    Introduction


     1.0 Introduction


          This  document  describes  the  fundamental  design  content  and
          functions to be implemented for an interface between Unix edition
          7  (Bell  Laboratories)  and  the  PDP-11  based   communications
          processor  (Tymshare  Distributed Systems), on Tymshare 'Dynasty'
          configurations.

          This  document  describes  the  environment  and  the  functional
          aspects  of  the  Unix  /  Local network node interface.  Another
          document   will   be   forthcoming,   describing   the    Dynasty
          configuration's functional requirements.

          The implementation of the  network  node  is  intended  to  allow
          multiplexed  input  into a host system (in this case Unix) and to
          allow diverse host systems to be included in  a  general  network
          configuration.    A  minimal  configuration  would  be  one  host
          connected to one network node which multiplexes  terminal  input.
          Logical  extensions  to  this  configuration  are the addition of
          other nodes daisy-chained or connected directly to the host,  and
          the  addition  of  logical  links  to  foreign  networks (such as
          Tymnet) to the node.

          The functionality described herein is intended to allow the above
          configurations  to  be  created with minimal modification to Unix
          yet to operate efficiently under reasonable load.   To  this  end
          the  interface  design  considers  most  sockets available on the
          network to be ttys and as such to be subject to the general  Unix
          tty character handling scheme.
